Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes. Peel and chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Peel and trim the @carrot{1}(peeled and trimmed), then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} stems lengthways. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

While the potatoes simmer, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the carrot and onion. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the veg has softened, transfer to a #small bowl{}, then pop your pan back on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} to the pan and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the cooked veg back to the pan along with the garlic. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Pour the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1/2%can} into the beef pan, then stir in the @red wine jus paste{22%g}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Once the potatoes are drained, add the @creme fraiche{75%g} and Cheddar to the pan and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Once the pie filling has thickened, season to taste, then remove from the heat. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick, then transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Top the filling with an even layer of mash and smooth it out using the back of a spoon.

Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, then pop under the grill until golden brown, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wash out your frying pan and pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the broccoli. Stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}, then add a splash of water. Pop a lid on the pan, or cover in foil, and cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir through the @unsalted butter{10%g}.

Serve your ultimate cottage pie with the buttery Tenderstem® alongside. Enjoy!